div.p:
My Friends, whilst the Sense of this Distress, that is coming as a Dreadful Visitation from the Hand of the Displeased God upon this Ungodly Land to Stain its Glory, Bring down its Pride and Punish its Forgetfulness of the Lord and his many Delivenantes, lay so Heavy upon my Spirit, the Lord presented before me all the Truly Conscientious and Well-inclined people in these Nations; and more especially You, his Despised but Chosen Generation, for whose sake he would yet have Mercy. And in the midst of his Judgments, This I received for you from the Lord, as his Holy Will and Counsel, and it often sprung in my Heart with a very Fresh and Strong Life;


TO THY TENTS, O ISRAEL!


TO THY TENTS, O ISRAEL!
